  "reasoning": "In the call_allocate() function at line 1610, the code uses au_cslack (call slack) to calculate the RPC response buffer size (rq_rcvsize), but it should use au_rslack (response slack). The au_cslack is for request authentication overhead, while au_rslack is for response authentication overhead. Using the wrong slack value causes incorrect response buffer allocation, leading to buffer boundary misalignment in XDR decoding. This is confirmed by fs/nfs/nfs3xdr.c line 116 which correctly uses au_rslack for response buffer calculation. The bug manifests as inode revalidate failures when getattr responses are incorrectly parsed due to buffer size miscalculation."
}

